subSubSection.paragraph:
Elytra parallel, narrow, not widened posteriorly; shoulders distinct; apices evenly rounded and distinctly depressed (
Fig. 42
); lamellate appendage consisting of two parts, horizontal, being oval and bearing a bunch of fine light curved hairs, and a vertical part which is rounded distally (
Figs. 26, 27
); upper side of elytral depression slightly pointed, slightly produced, the lower side slightly emarginate and rounded; surface shining, very densely punctured and microsculptured, covered with fine, short light and adpressed pubescence and sparse semierect dark setae.

